An Overland Park man was sentenced in U.S. District Court to 5 years and 3 months in prison for buying child pornography from a supplier in Italy, prosecutors said this afternoon.
Daniel Aldridge, 57, also must pay a $12,500 fine. He pleaded guilty to one count of receiving child pornography.
Investigators found Aldridge’s name in the suppliers’ email. An undercover U.S. Postal Inspection Service agent then offered to sell him child pornography. Prosecutors said in a statement that Aldridge asked for a catalog and ordered six CDs of images described as showing sex acts by girls as young as 10 years old.
| The Star
